The w3c-validator-to-rally is a gem that ready an inputed URL and return all W3C Errors on this URL and the user can create a defect on Rally, one by each defect founded.

Install:

Just type in your command-line:

"gem install w3c-validator-to-rally"

or download the gem(disponible in this repo, and install manually).

Usage:

This gem is divided in two parts: W3CValidator and Rally.

To init the W3C part, create a variable and init her.

"W3CValidatorToRally::W3CValidator.new"



To init the Rally part, create another variable(or use the same variable) and set:

"W3CValidatorToRally::Rally.new"
